Company description: Hapag-Lloyd Cruises gilt im deutschsprachigen Raum als führende Kreuzfahrtmarke im Luxus- und Expeditionsbereich. Zur Flotte gehören aktuell fünf Schiffe. Unsere Schiffe sind klein, individuell und herausragend in ihrer Klasse: Die weltweit besten Luxusschiffe EUROPA und EUROPA 2, die als einzige vom Berlitz Cruise Guide mit der Höchstnote 5-Sterne-Plus* ausgezeichnet sind, bilden zusammen die EUROPA-Klasse von Hapag-Lloyd Cruises. Sie steht für ein Reiseerlebnis auf höchstem Niveau mit hervorragender Servicekultur, vielfältiger Kulinarik und außergewöhnlichem Routing rund um die ganze Welt. Im Expeditionssegment sind wir mit drei modernen Schiffen auf Wachstumskurs: Die HANSEATIC nature und HANSEATIC inspiration, die ersten zwei der aus drei Schiffen bestehenden neuen Expeditionsklasse, sind 2019 in Dienst gestellt worden. Im Jahr 2021 vervollständigte die HANSEATIC spirit die Flotte. Die neue Expeditionsklasse verfügt über moderne Umwelttechnik wie SCR-Katalysatoren und ist für die Nutzung von Landstrom ausgestattet. Die höchste Eisklasse und ein niedriger Tiefgang ermöglichen sowohl Routen in die polaren Regionen Arktis und Antarktis, als auch in Warmwasser-Destinationen wie den Amazonas.

Company description: Norwegian Travel is a premier provider of high-quality experiential tourism in Norway, specializing in a diverse range of activities that highlight the country's stunning natural landscapes and rich cultural heritage. The company operates year-round, offering unforgettable experiences that cater to both summer and winter enthusiasts. From exhilarating dog sledding and snowmobiling in the winter to serene kayaking and fjord cruises in the summer, Norwegian Travel ensures that adventure seekers and nature lovers alike can immerse themselves in the breathtaking beauty of Norway. With a mission to deliver authentic experiences, Norwegian Travel partners with local guides and activity centers, providing guests with expert knowledge and a genuine connection to the region's culture and wildlife. This collaboration not only enhances the quality of the experiences offered but also supports local communities and promotes sustainable tourism practices. The company is committed to environmental responsibility, utilizing electric transportation options and promoting eco-friendly practices throughout its operations. Norwegian Travel's target market includes adventure seekers, families, and cultural enthusiasts from both local and international backgrounds, all looking for memorable experiences in Norway's picturesque environments. The company’s offerings also include unique cultural encounters, such as interactions with the indigenous Sami people and their reindeer, further enriching the travel experience. With a user-friendly online booking system and a strong presence on social media, Norwegian Travel strives to inspire travelers to explore the majestic fjords, vibrant city life, and serene wilderness of Norway. By focusing on customer satisfaction and safety, Norwegian Travel aims to create lasting memories for its clients, making it an ideal choice for those seeking to discover the wonders of Northern Norway.

Company description: Wilhelmsen Group is a leading player in the maritime industry with over 50 years of experience, specializing in ship management and a wide array of maritime services. The company is dedicated to shaping the future of the maritime sector by delivering exceptional customer experiences, with a strong emphasis on innovation, sustainability, and the continuous development of its workforce. Serving a diverse clientele that includes ship owners and operators across various sectors such as bulk carriers, cruise ships, and LNG carriers, Wilhelmsen ensures safe and efficient operations while adhering to international regulations. With a presence in over 70 countries and access to more than 2,200 ports, Wilhelmsen offers a comprehensive range of services and solutions that enhance the efficiency and safety of maritime operations. The company’s mission is to provide exceptional customer experiences through innovative solutions, while its vision is centered on driving sustainability and digitalization within the maritime sector. Recognizing that the dedication and expertise of its employees are central to its success, Wilhelmsen places significant importance on its workforce. The company is committed to fostering long-term partnerships and contributing positively to global trade and environmental stewardship. By leveraging its extensive distribution network and expertise in regulatory compliance, Wilhelmsen aims to reduce operational complexity for its partners, allowing them to focus on their core business. Additionally, through initiatives like the Motion Ventures Fund, Wilhelmsen actively invests in technological advancements that support decarbonization and operational efficiency, reinforcing its role as a catalyst for change in the maritime industry.

Shipping today is a leading company in shipping and forwarding, with over 600 employees and overseas companies in Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Hungary, Montenegro, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Turkiye. Company description: NRV is a leading travel company based in the Netherlands, specializing in unique round trips and cruises to a diverse array of global destinations. Founded in 2006, NRV has established itself as the largest round trip specialist in the country, offering approximately 500 meticulously curated journeys to over 50 destinations worldwide, including Africa, Asia, Europe, the Middle East, and the Americas. The company's mission, encapsulated in its name "Nederland Reist Voordelig," is to provide travelers with the best value for their money, ensuring a balanced mix of cultural and natural experiences. NRV caters to a wide demographic, including families, groups, and individual travelers, offering various travel options such as group tours, private trips, and family vacations. With a strong emphasis on customer satisfaction and service, NRV partners with reputable cruise lines like Holland America Line, known for its exceptional service and diverse dining options, to enhance the travel experience. The company is dedicated to creating memorable journeys that combine adventure and relaxation, allowing travelers to immerse themselves in the rich biodiversity and culture of destinations like Panama, Costa Rica, and the Caribbean. NRV's target market primarily consists of Dutch-speaking travelers who seek both cultural exploration and leisure in their travels. In addition to its focus on providing unforgettable experiences, NRV is committed to promoting responsible tourism practices and minimizing the environmental impact of its cruises. The organization works closely with various partners, including hotels and excursion providers, to offer a wide range of accommodations and activities tailored to the desires of its clients. With over 15 years of experience in the travel industry, NRV continues to innovate and expand its offerings, ensuring that every journey begins with comfort and enjoyment while creating lasting memories for its clients.

Company description: CSMART, Center for Simulator Maritime Training, is the international maritime training center of the Carnival Corporation & plc Group.  With its scale, technology and equipment, and training approach, CSMART is the most progressive maritime center of its kind in the world for training and continually improving industry-wide safety, sustainability and operational excellence.  CSMART's mission is to be a leader in developing and delivering the best professional training, and set the global standard in maritime training by: • Providing high quality maritime training services for industry-wide safety, sustainability and operational excellence  • Developing training courses that optimize learning and maximize cost-effectiveness  • Researching and developing training courses to meet the changing needs of the maritime industry  • Providing the latest relevant simulation and training equipment • Using stringent quality assurance criteria to determine concepts and procedures for training courses  In June 2018, CSMART Academy has been recognized as the world's first Center of Safety Excellence by DNV-GL, the world's leading classification society and a recognized advisor for the maritime industry. The CSMART Academy and corresponding CSMART hotel are both located at the Arison Maritime Center in Almere, The Netherlands. About Carnival Corporation & plc Group: Carnival Corporation & plc Group is the largest leisure travel company in the world, with 9 cruise brands worldwide consisting of: Carnival Cruise Line, Holland America Line, Princess Cruises, Seabourn, AIDA Cruises, Costa Cruises, Cunard, P&O Cruises Australia and P&O Cruises UK. Together, these brands operate 100+ ships visiting over 700 ports around the world and welcoming over 11.5 million guests annually.

Company description: The port of Aarhus is an active trade area with approx. 150 companies, creating the basis for about 10,000 jobs. The port of Aarhus is Denmark’s largest container port, with a market share of about 60 per cent, and also Denmark’s largest public bulk port. This implies that a very large part of the consumer goods are imported to Denmark via the port of Aarhus. Also, a significant part of the Danish export is shipped via the fine-meshed network of shipping routes to all parts of the world. In addition, the port of Aarhus is an important ferry port, serving around 1,3 million cars and around 2,9 million passengers on an annual basis - plus an increasing number of cruise passengers.  You´ll find Port of Aarhus office at Vandvejen 7, 8000 Aarhus C.

Company description: La società Riccardo Sanges & c. è stata fondata nel 1929.  Da quella data Riccardo Sanges & c. esercita la propria attività d’impresa nel territorio nazionale e internazionale. Riccardo Sanges & c. S.r.l. svolge oggi fondamentalmente due tipi di attività d’impresa.  Una commerciale riguardante il commercio degli idrocarburi ed una industriale e di servizi legata all’industria marittima, portuale e dei trasporti. Più nel dettaglio con riferimento all’attività commerciale Riccardo Sanges & c. è concessionaria “Eni gas gpl” per le provincie di Trapani ed Agrigento ed anche concessionaria “ENI fuel” con la gestione diretta di 5 impianti nel porto e nella città di Trapani. Con riferimento invece all’attività industriale e di servizi Riccardo Sanges & c. è impresa portuale autorizzata (terminal operator) per lo sbarco, imbarco e movimentazione di merci nei porti di Trapani e Mazara del Vallo. Riccardo Sanges & c., inoltre, sin dal 1929 esercita l’attività di agenzia marittima, broker marittimo, spedizioniere e doganalista con ormai una consolidata presenza in tutti i porti del territorio nazionale. Infine attraverso l’insegna “Panfalone viaggi”, Riccardo Sanges & c. dal 1990 opera con l’attività di agenzia di viaggi e turismo e di tour operator. Nell’ambito di queste ultime attività d’impresa, recentemente si è acquisita un’interessante specializzazione nelle escursioni riguardanti le navi crociere.

Company description: Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. was founded in 1997 by the Venice Port Authority in order to manage and improve cruise traffic in the Port of Venice. The Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A.  operates in the Marittima and S. Basilio areas which stretch over a surface altogether of more than 244.000 sq. m. of which the Terminals occupy  53.000 sq. m. The maritime basin in the Marittima area measures circa 123.700 sq.m.   The shareholders of Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. are the following: APV Investimenti S.p.A., Finpax S.r.l., SAVE S.p.A. (Venice Marco Polo Airport), Veneto Sviluppo S.p.A., the Venice Chamber of Commerce  and the Venice Municipality. In addition Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. is the majority shareholder of two specialized companies: Venice Yacht Pier S.r.l. (V.Y.P.) founded to increase yachting in Venice and Venice Yachts and Ship Assistance (V.Y.S.A.) dedicated to the promotion of services for the maxi-yachts market. The growing needs of cruise traffic and Venice's appeal as a cultural and tourist attraction have given rise to the radical transformation of the Port area starting from 1997 as a result of the joint effort of Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A. and the Venice Port Authority. Such transformation is exemplified by the renovation of ancient port buildings once dedicated to the commercial traffic, which have now become modern and multi-purpose facilities. Venezia Terminal Passeggeri S.p.A.'s port facilities cater the needs of any ship berthing in Venice.  ·          The Ferry Terminal 123 assists ferries for the Eastern Mediterranean area  ·          The S. Basilio Terminal accommodates medium-size cruise ships, mega-yachts and high speed hydrofoils  ·          Cruise Terminals 103, 107/108, 117 and Terminal Isonzo in the Marittima area are multi-purpose facilities which, additionally to their original purpose, are utilised for hosting meetings, conventions and fairs.

Company description: DERPART Reisevertrieb GmbH ist eine der führenden Reisevertriebsorganisationen in Deutschland, die ein starkes Franchise-System mit rund 290 Reisebüros und 60 Business Travel Agenturen bildet. Das Unternehmen hat sich der Mission verschrieben, seinen Franchise-Nehmern als vertrauensvoller Partner zur Seite zu stehen, um deren unternehmerische Ziele zu erreichen, während sie ihre Individualität und Freiheit bewahren. DERPART bietet ein umfangreiches Leistungspaket, das Marketing, IT, Weiterbildung und Unterstützung im Shop-Konzept umfasst, um den Partnern zu helfen, ihre Erfolgspotenziale zu maximieren. Die Zielgruppe des Unternehmens umfasst sowohl private Reisende als auch Geschäftsreisende, wobei die Agenturen maßgeschneiderte Lösungen für verschiedene Reisebedürfnisse anbieten. Als Teil der DERTOUR Group, die zur REWE Group gehört, profitiert DERPART von einer starken Markenbekanntheit und umfangreichen Ressourcen, die es den Partnern ermöglichen, in einem wettbewerbsintensiven Markt erfolgreich zu sein. Das Unternehmen bietet eine breite Palette an Reiseleistungen, darunter Urlaubsreisen, Geschäftsreisen, Kreuzfahrten und Gruppenreisen. Mit einer starken Ausrichtung auf Kundenservice und individuelle Beratung hat sich DERPART als vertrauenswürdiger Partner für Reisende etabliert.  Die Mission von DERPART ist es, unvergessliche Reiseerlebnisse zu schaffen, indem sie ihren Kunden maßgeschneiderte Lösungen und erstklassigen Service bieten. Um dies zu erreichen, arbeitet das Unternehmen eng mit renommierten Fluggesellschaften, Hotels und Reiseveranstaltern zusammen, um seinen Kunden die besten Angebote und Reiseerlebnisse zu garantieren. DERPART richtet sich an ein breites Publikum, von Familien über Geschäftsreisende bis hin zu Gruppen, und ist gut positioniert, um den wachsenden Anforderungen des Reisemarktes gerecht zu werden. Mit mehreren Standorten und einem engagierten Team von Experten ist DERPART bereit, die Zukunft des Reisens aktiv mitzugestalten.

Company description: MARTEC MARINE is part of an Italian privately owned Group active in the Defense and Integrated Safety solutions for Navy, Cruise ships and Mega Yachts since 1994. From the early beginning of its activities Martec has deeply invested in the design and development of safety systems, being awarded, at present, as one of the most skilled companies in an international context, in this field. More than 12 Navy ships and more than 80 Cruise liners and Mega Yachts have Martec Damage Control Systems installed. Product range vary from hardware (Damage Control Systems, Electronic Incident Board, Fire Detection System, Emergency Shutdown System, Automatic Fire Sensing and Suppression System) to software packages (Damage Control, Decision Support, On Board Stability, Personnel Tracking, Security and Technical Patrol Management, Injured Treatment). Innovation, Integration and Flexibility are the key words for MARTEC: development of new solutions based on customer requirements, integration with third parties’ Ship Automation Systems and any type of safety subsystems, flexibility to implement any customization are our strength. All native MARTEC Systems are designed for integration in a Total Safety concept. Software packages are designed to present all different subsystem (regardless of the manufacturer) through a unique Vectorial Man Machine Interface, with zoom, pan and touch screen features. Software modules can be provided with the hardware or embedded in the Automation software. On-board safety centers, remote control shore safety centers as well as shore based simulation and training rooms complete the range of solutions. The Group organization include 2 branch offices in Italy for Italian Navy and 1 subsidiary in the US for customer support, 1 R&D branch office in Italy, a Software House and a Hardware Design and Production company.

Company description: We bring the internet to ships. At scale, with speed, and without compromise. Nowhere Networks is a Swedish high-tech company building the world’s most powerful land-based maritime broadband network. We deliver fast, reliable, and cost-effective internet connectivity to ferries, cruise ships, and cargo vessels - across Europe and expanding globally. But we’re not just a connectivity provider. We’re a full-stack operator. We design, build, install, and run everything ourselves. From our smart antennas and cloud-based network platform to onboard Wi-Fi portals and traffic management software. Our hybrid approach - combining land-based radio, LEO satellite, LTE, and port connectivity- is unmatched in the industry. Trusted by some of the biggest names in shipping and cruising (Stena Line, Tallink/Silja Line, DFDS, Irish Ferries, Gotland Alandia Cruises and more), we connect over 150 vessels and serve more than 100 million passengers annually. Whether it’s crew comms, passenger Wi-Fi, or real-time fleet operations, we make sure it all runs smoothly - and fast. We’re engineers, entrepreneurs, and problem-solvers who love building great tech and solving real-world challenges at sea. If you do too, come work with us.

Company description: DDSG Blue Danube Schiffahrt GmbH is a premier river cruise company based in Vienna, specializing in scenic cruises along the Danube River, particularly in the stunning Wachau region. Operating from March 30 to November 3, 2024, the company offers a diverse range of sightseeing cruises that cater to both leisure travelers and families. With a modern fleet of nine well-equipped ships, DDSG Blue Danube is dedicated to providing unforgettable experiences on the water, combining relaxation, culinary delights, and entertainment for its guests. The onboard dining experience is managed by three partner businesses, ensuring high-quality, seasonal cuisine that enhances the overall cruise experience and highlights local Wachau specialties. The company targets a wide audience, including local and international tourists, families, groups, and individuals seeking unique leisure activities along the Danube River. As a successor to the historic Erste Donau-Dampfschiffahrts-Gesellschaft founded in 1829, DDSG Blue Danube continues to uphold a legacy of excellence in river navigation and hospitality. Its mission is to provide memorable and enjoyable experiences on the water, emphasizing quality service and customer satisfaction. By collaborating with various partners, DDSG Blue Danube enhances the overall travel experience, allowing guests to explore the region's rich cultural heritage. Through its commitment to excellence, DDSG Blue Danube Schiffahrt GmbH aims to be a leading choice for river tourism in Austria, inviting guests to discover the beauty and charm of the Danube River.

Company description: OLIVER DESIGN es una compañía especializada en diseño y arquitectura naval, fundada en 1990 por el ingeniero naval Jaime Oliver. Graduado en 1964, inició su trayectoria con el diseño de grandes buques para el histórico astillero La Naval de Sestao (Bizkaia), para posteriormente fundar su propia empresa de construcción de embarcaciones de recreo, Yates Revilo, que a lo largo de casi una década llevó a cabo cerca de una treintena de proyectos. En 1978 creó su propia oficina técnica, desde la que continuó desarrollando proyectos innovadores para armadores y astilleros de todo el mundo. A partir de 1990 puso en marcha la nueva firma OLIVER DESIGN, con el objetivo de potenciar su proyección internacional. En pocos años la empresa multiplicó y diversifico su actividad para abarcar no sólo el proyecto, sino la habilitación de interiores e incluso superestructuras completas, buscando proporcionar un servicio integral a sus clientes. Iñigo Oliver, Director General se incorporó a la empresa en el año 1987 y su hijo Iñi Oliver lleva trabajando en Oliver Design desde el año 2015 después de graduarse con honores como Arquitecto Naval en la Universidad de Southampton OLIVER DESIGN está en disposición de asumir todas las tareas previas a la puesta en servicio de buques de cualquier tipo. Su catálogo de servicios incluye labores especializadas en diferentes áreas desde el diseño conceptual hasta la supervisión de obra pasando por todo el desarrollo del proyecto arquitéctónico y diseño de interiores. El principal valor añadido de OLIVER DESIGN es la creación de proyectos singulares con un alto grado de innovación y diseño contando con un catálogo de proyectos con más de 400 barcos de la más variada tipología a lo largo de 25 años: desde buques escuela a yates de recreo y de turismo, pasando por barcos de transporte, pesqueros, dragas, ferris, cruceros, etc. La trayectoria de la empresa está avalada por múltiples reconocimientos y galardones internacionales, entre ellos varios Premios Shippax de diseño naval. OLIVER DESIGN ocupa un emplazamiento singular. Alejada de polígonos industriales y de oficinas en el centro de la ciudad, la empresa proyectó y construyó una sede integrada en su entorno natural. Se ubica en Getxo (Bizkaia), a muy poca distancia de los acantilados de la Galea, una atalaya sobre el Golfo de Bizkaia que da acceso al Puerto de Bilbao, el más importante del Norte de España desde su fundación en el siglo XIII. La compañía cuenta también con delegaciones en Santander y Cádiz.

Company description: The European Sea Ports Organisation was founded in 1993. It  represents the port authorities, port associations and port administrations of the seaports of the Member States of the European Union and Norway. ESPO has also observer members in several neighbouring countries to the EU. The European Union simply cannot function without its seaports. 90 % of Europe’s cargo trade in goods passes through the more than 1200 seaports existing in the 23 maritime Member States of the EU and more than 400 million passengers pass through Europe’s ports every year using ferry and cruise services. Without seaports, the European Union would not exist as an economic world power. Without seaports, there would be no internal market. ESPO ensures that seaports have a clear voice in the European Union. The organisation promotes the common interests of its members throughout Europe and is also engaged in dialogue with European stakeholders in the Port and Maritime sector. ESPO works through a permanent secretariat in Brussels, a General Assembly, an Executive Committee, and 8 specialised committees.

Aboa Mare Training Center offers a wide range of courses both for professional seafarers and leisure-time boaters. In order to be able to offer a wide range of courses and satisfy the requirements of our clients, we have a large network of experts on diverse fields within seafaring. Today we have several international customers and we have a close co-operation with Wärtsilä and ABB which give us the knowledge of training international crews. Aboa Mare is STCW audited by the Finnish Transport Safety Agency. Part of our education is audited by the DNV ISO 9001 standard. Aboa Mare offers training in safety at sea and environmentally sustainable development issues related to seafaring. We focus on providing simulator-based training for maritime students, shipping companies, authorities including pilots and sea rescuers as well as for leisure boating. In the simulations we use different shipmodels, e.g. large cruise ships, tankers and smaller archipelago ferries. The simulations are conducted on Finnish coastal areas and lakes as well as on the most heavily trafficked routes worldwide. The simulation resources consist of 9 simulator bridges, engine room simulators, VTS simulator, DP simulator and radio simulator. We can offer training on Consilium, Furuno, Wärtsilä, Transas and Sperry Marine bridges in our simulator. With the simulator interface we have developed we can generate technical faults to the real navigational instruments on the bridges.

Las regatas se realizan en barcos de clase crucero.

Name: Zeeland Cruise Port B.V.
Technologies: Joomla
Company description: Zeeland Cruise Port The Port of Zeeland is located on the Western Scheldt estuary, between Rotterdam and Antwerp, and has an open connection to the North Sea. The port itself is made up of the port of Vlissingen, located on the northern shore of the estuary, and the port of Terneuzen on the southern side. Due to its strategic position, this port is one of the most ideally situated harbors in northwestern Europe. A wide variety of full and half-day shore excursions starting from the port where cruise ships are accommodated are possible. All locations are within an hour’s drive of the port. Discover Zeeland  Zeeland, a province of the Netherlands, is situated on the North Sea coast in the far southwest of the country. Two mighty estuaries transect it: the Eastern Scheldt (in Dutch Oosterschelde) and the Western Scheldt (in Dutch Westerschelde). The province is made up of water, islands and peninsulas. Zeeland’s open, panoramic scenery is impressive. The countryside is made up largely of farmland and wetlands. Small towns and villages, many of them historic and scattered across the countryside, form the characteristic landscape.  Sparkling Cities Vlissingen is situated on the mouth of the Western Scheldt estuary and is famous for its seaside boulevards in the southern district. From here, you can see and, almost, touch the ships passing by on their way to and from the ports of Vlissingen, Ghent and Antwerp; ranging from the smallest seagoing vessels through the largest container carriers. The town has a rich history of fishery, (slave) trading, shipbuilding and piracy, as you can see on a visit to one of its museums or Het Arsenaal theme park. Throughout its history Vlissingen has been besieged many times by armies and floods, both of which destroyed some of its historic buildings and squares. Those that survived have been – and still are – restored with great love and skill.
